<br>
Cold Spells<br>
<br>
I honestly can't count how many times this has been brought up.  We simply don't get cold spells because we aren't as versitile at nuking as wizards.  In some ways it seems not even as druids.  Roleplaying reason or not, we've been told straight out over and over we won't get it.  I'm happy enough with fire and magic personally.<br>
<br>
Lure anti summoned<br>
<br>
Slight increase in damage and making them lure are almost needed.  Damage factor would help for those spells we have now and in further expansions that do so much damage.  And lure based?  Well theres no few summoned mobs out there that it better also be lure based to make them worth wasting a slot for.  Honestly.. would you mem a spell only good against one type of mob if it's about the same as your other DDs that work on everything?  Only in the hole would it be semi useful.  And honestly.. even with those two changes, I could still see people using SoFB over it.  Since it's conj based.<br>
<br>
1600 Bolt<br>
<br>
This plays hand in  hand with the &quot;every 10 levels damage from DDs doubles (approx).&quot;  It's pretty much true.  Our level 44 DD which was the best up to level 50 is not eclipsed doubly by Shock of Fiery Blades.  Or even shock of the sun.  (Even though it isn't in the game.)<br>
<br>
The only argument against making a 1600 bolt is that crazy bug that doubles bolt damage.  If you got some crits on those &quot;double bolts&quot; you'd be doing very close to manaburn damage.  And yeah thats some crazy one shot kill stuff.  (even if you have to be very lucky.)<br>
<br>
There isn't really another good reason why not.  If the bolt has a long casting time, and well it is a bolt.  People normally don't use it.  It takes so long to cast, it doesn't always hit, and worse yet for some people, it's evoc.  But it would fill the gap from lava bolt to a solid 60th level one.  Would put us above druids too for sheer damage, although again wholey unpractical for the most part.<br>
<br>
And last.. This spell merely has to exist for most of us to be happy, not be easily obtainable.<br>
<br>
Gate Shoes<br>
<br>
Oh and those shoes.  Yeah thats cool, but you put an ability in like this and it completely undermines the current usefulness of gate objects.  Such as potions, very rare items that gate, etc.  Soon as a mage can summon something for free, people are far more inclined to track down a high level mage and get it summoned rather than pay their precious plat.<br>
<br>
Think of it this way.. Anything that a potion can do that we can't already.. We won't be able to do.  Thats about as simple as it gets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uultimusbible.showPublicProfile?language=EN>UltimusBible</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(7/23/02 2:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1391.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Some responses</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The only argument against making a 1600 bolt is that crazy bug that doubles bolt damage. If you got some crits on those &quot;double bolts&quot; you'd be doing very close to manaburn damage. And yeah thats some crazy one shot kill stuff. (even if you have to be very lucky.)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
